1d:["$","div",null,{"className":"markdown-container","children":[["$","h1","h1-0",{"children":"Research Frontiers in Automation"}],"\n",["$","p","p-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Version"}],": 2.0 | ",["$","strong","strong-1",{"children":"Last Updated"}],": 2026-05-07",["$","br","br-0",{}],"\n",["$","strong","strong-2",{"children":"Scope"}],": Open problems with current state-of-the-art, key papers, and why each frontier matters"]}],"\n",["$","hr","hr-0",{}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-0",{"children":"See Also"}],"\n",["$","ul","ul-0",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":[["$","a","a-0",{"href":"../3_The_Applications/3.9_AI_Driven_Automation.md","children":"AI-Driven Automation"}]," — foundation models and physical AI"]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":[["$","a","a-0",{"href":"4.2_Ethics_and_Society.md","children":"Ethics and Society"}]," — frontier #8 (autonomous policy)"]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":[["$","a","a-0",{"href":"4.3_Learning_Roadmap.md","children":"Learning Roadmap"}]," — months 5-6 (safe RL) and 9-10 (advanced specialization)"]}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","hr","hr-1",{}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-1",{"children":"1. Safe Reinforcement Learning for Physical Systems"}],"\n",["$","p","p-1",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Why it matters"}],": Learned controllers can outperform hand-coded systems but provide no formal safety guarantee. Deploying RL in safety-critical automation (medical robots, autonomous vehicles, industrial machinery) without certification is commercially and legally untenable."]}],"\n",["$","p","p-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Current state-of-the-art (2025)"}],":"]}],"\n",["$","ul","ul-1",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Constrained MDPs (CMDPs) achieve 97.8% task success while maintaining safety constraints on benchmark tasks [Wachi et al., 2024]."}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"Control Barrier Functions (CBF): Formally certify that state trajectories remain within a safe set. Now integrated with neural network policies using differentiable CBFs [Ames et al., 2019; Dawson et al., 2023]."}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"Shielding: A safety monitor overrides unsafe actions in real time. Neural shield synthesis scales shielding to high-dimensional policies [Hasanbeig et al., 2023]."}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":"Safe RL benchmark: Safety Gymnasium 2.0 (2024) — standardized environments with constraint specifications. Performance: best methods achieve <5% constraint violations."}],"\n",["$","li","li-4",{"children":"Lyapunov-based RL: Ensures system stability (Lyapunov decrease condition) rather than just constraint satisfaction [Berkenkamp et al., 2017]."}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","p","p-3",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Open questions"}],":"]}],"\n",["$","ul","ul-2",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"How to certify learned controllers for arbitrary nonlinear systems at scale? (Formal verification of large neural networks remains NP-hard in general.)"}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"Can safety and optimality be balanced without excessive conservatism? (Safety often reduces reward by 10–30%.)"}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"How to provide safety certificates that regulatory bodies (FDA, FAA, NHTSA) will actually accept?"}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":"How to compose safety guarantees across multiple interacting learned systems?"}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","p","p-4",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Key papers"}],":"]}],"\n",["$","ul","ul-3",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":["Garcia, J. & Fernández, F. (2015). Comprehensive survey on safe RL. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"JMLR"}],", 16(1), 1437-1480."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":["Ames, A.D. et al. (2019). Control Barrier Functions: Theory and Applications. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"ECC 2019"}],"."]}],"\n","$L26","\n","$L27","\n","$L28","\n"]}],"\n","$L29","\n","$L2a","\n","$L2b","\n","$L2c","\n","$L2d","\n","$L2e","\n","$L2f","\n","$L30","\n","$L31","\n","$L32","\n","$L33","\n","$L34","\n","$L35","\n","$L36","\n","$L37","\n","$L38","\n","$L39","\n","$L3a","\n","$L3b","\n","$L3c","\n","$L3d","\n","$L3e","\n","$L3f","\n","$L40","\n","$L41","\n","$L42","\n","$L43","\n","$L44","\n","$L45","\n","$L46","\n","$L47","\n","$L48","\n","$L49","\n","$L4a","\n","$L4b","\n","$L4c","\n","$L4d","\n","$L4e","\n","$L4f","\n","$L50","\n","$L51","\n","$L52","\n","$L53","\n","$L54","\n","$L55","\n","$L56","\n","$L57","\n","$L58","\n","$L59","\n","$L5a","\n","$L5b","\n","$L5c","\n","$L5d","\n","$L5e","\n","$L5f","\n","$L60","\n","$L61","\n","$L62","\n","$L63","\n","$L64","\n","$L65","\n","$L66","\n","$L67","\n","$L68","\n","$L69","\n","$L6a","\n","$L6b","\n","$L6c","\n","$L6d","\n","$L6e","\n","$L6f","\n","$L70","\n","$L71","\n","$L72","\n","$L73","\n","$L74","\n","$L75","\n","$L76","\n","$L77","\n","$L78","\n","$L79","\n","$L7a","\n","$L7b","\n","$L7c","\n","$L7d","\n","$L7e","\n","$L7f","\n","$L80","\n","$L81","\n","$L82","\n","$L83","\n","$L84","\n","$L85","\n","$L86","\n","$L87","\n","$L88","\n","$L89","\n","$L8a","\n","$L8b","\n","$L8c","\n","$L8d","\n","$L8e","\n","$L8f","\n","$L90","\n","$L91","\n","$L92","\n","$L93","\n","$L94","\n","$L95","\n","$L96","\n","$L97"]}]
