2a:["$","h2","h2-2",{"children":"2. Robust Sim-to-Real Transfer"}]
2b:["$","p","p-5",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Why it matters"}],": Real robot training data is expensive, slow, and risky. Simulation is cheap and safe—but a policy trained in simulation often fails on real hardware due to visual and dynamics differences (the \"reality gap\"). Bridging this gap is prerequisite to scalable robot learning."]}]
2c:["$","p","p-6",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Current state-of-the-art (2025)"}],":"]}]
2d:["$","ul","ul-4",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Domain randomization: Randomize simulation physics, textures, lighting during training. Achieves <3% performance gap on dexterous manipulation benchmarks [Tobin et al., 2017; Akkaya et al., 2019 (OpenAI Rubik's cube)]."}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"System identification: Estimate real-world parameters (friction, mass, motor constants) and inject into simulation. IROS 2024 best paper used differentiable simulation for gradient-based system ID."}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"Real2Sim2Real: Use real data to refine simulation; iterate. Meta's Habitat 3.0 (2023) demonstrates this for indoor navigation."}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":"Adaptive domain randomization: Learn which randomizations matter using meta-learning (DROID dataset, 2024)."}],"\n",["$","li","li-4",{"children":"Contact-rich manipulation: Remains hardest frontier—current sim2real for multi-fingered grasping: 50–70% success rate (vs. 95%+ in sim)."}],"\n"]}]
2e:["$","p","p-7",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Open questions"}],":"]}]
2f:["$","ul","ul-5",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Which specific randomizations transfer? Theory is largely absent; practitioners rely on trial and error."}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"How to transfer to completely different robot morphologies (sim to sim2real cross-embodiment)?"}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"Long-horizon tasks (100+ steps): Compounding errors across steps make extended manipulation extremely challenging."}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":"How to handle deformable objects (cloth, cables)? Differentiable simulation is advancing but contact dynamics remain imprecise."}],"\n"]}]
30:["$","p","p-8",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Key papers"}],":"]}]
31:["$","ul","ul-6",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":["Tobin, J. et al. (2017). Domain randomization for sim2real transfer. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"IROS 2017"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":["Akkaya, I. et al. (2019). Solving Rubik's Cube with a Robot Hand. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"arXiv:1910.07113"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":["Peng, X.B. et al. (2018). Sim-to-Real Transfer of Robotic Control with Dynamics Randomization. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"ICRA 2018"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":["Mehta, B. et al. (2020). Active Domain Randomization. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"CoRL 2020"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-4",{"children":["O'Neill, J. et al. (2023). Open X-Embodiment: Robotic Learning across Embodiments. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"arXiv:2310.08864"}],"."]}],"\n"]}]
32:["$","hr","hr-3",{}]
33:["$","h2","h2-3",{"children":"3. Formal Verification of Neural Network Controllers"}]
34:["$","p","p-9",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Why it matters"}],": Neural networks are the state-of-the-art for perception and control but lack the interpretability required for formal safety certification. Regulators (FAA Advisory Circular AC 20-115, EU AI Act) increasingly require \"safety assurance\" of AI systems in critical applications."]}]
35:["$","p","p-10",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Current state-of-the-art (2025)"}],":"]}]
36:["$","ul","ul-7",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"SMT-based verifiers: Reluplex [Katz et al., 2017], Marabou [Katz et al., 2022] — verify properties of ReLU networks by encoding as SMT problem. Scale: up to ~1M parameters with modern optimizations."}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"Abstract interpretation: CROWN [Zhang et al., 2018], DeepZ, α-CROWN — bound network outputs over input regions via linear relaxations. 100–10,000x faster than SMT."}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"Probabilistic verification: Conformal prediction provides probabilistic safety certificates with PAC (probably approximately correct) guarantees. More practical for large networks."}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":"NN-Lyapunov synthesis: Jointly learn neural Lyapunov functions and policies with verified stability [Chang et al., 2020]."}],"\n",["$","li","li-4",{"children":"Neural Architecture for Verifiability: Structured networks (monotone, Lipschitz-bounded) that are certifiable by design [Pauli et al., 2021]."}],"\n"]}]
37:["$","p","p-11",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Fundamental limitations"}],":"]}]
38:["$","ul","ul-8",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Verification complexity is exponential in network size for worst-case guarantees."}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"High-dimensional systems (image inputs): Current techniques scale to thousands of input dimensions, not millions (image pixels)."}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"No complete solution for arbitrary architectures with recurrence (RNNs, Transformers)."}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":"Abstraction gap: Formal model must accurately represent the real system; model mismatch defeats verification."}],"\n"]}]
39:["$","p","p-12",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Key papers"}],":"]}]
3a:["$","ul","ul-9",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":["Katz, G. et al. (2022). The Marabou Framework for Verification and Analysis of DNNs. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"CAV 2022"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":["Zhang, H. et al. (2018). Efficient Neural Network Robustness Certification with General Activation Functions. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"NeurIPS 2018"}]," (CROWN)."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":["Liu, C. et al. (2021). Algorithms for Verifying Deep Neural Networks. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"Foundations and Trends in Optimization"}],"."]}],"\n"]}]
3b:["$","hr","hr-4",{}]
3c:["$","h2","h2-4",{"children":"4. Human-Robot Collaboration (HRC)"}]
3d:["$","p","p-13",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Why it matters"}],": Cobots (collaborative robots) share workspaces with humans in manufacturing, healthcare, and service settings. Ensuring safety, productivity, and ergonomics simultaneously is an unsolved multi-objective optimization problem. ISO/TS 15066 establishes speed-and-separation monitoring but doesn't address cognitive safety."]}]
3e:["$","p","p-14",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Current state-of-the-art (2025)"}],":"]}]
3f:["$","ul","ul-10",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Force/torque limiting: ISO/TS 15066 defines maximum contact forces for ISO 10218-compliant cobots. Universal Robots, KUKA, ABB cobots enforce this in hardware."}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"Intent prediction: Neural networks predict human motion trajectories 0.5–2 seconds ahead with 85% accuracy at 1m range [Pfeiffer et al., 2018; Mangos et al., 2023]."}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"Shared autonomy: Robot infers human goal from partial observations and assists proactively; human and robot jointly control without explicit communication [Javdani et al., 2018]."}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":"Natural language interaction: LLM-powered interfaces allow workers to give tasks verbally. \"Bring me the nearest red component\" resolves without pre-programming."}],"\n",["$","li","li-4",{"children":"Ergonomics: ML models predict worker fatigue from motion capture, suggest task reallocation before injury [Lorenzini et al., 2023]."}],"\n"]}]
40:["$","p","p-15",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Amazon (2025) stat update"}],": 750,000+ robots in global fulfillment; primarily AMRs for shelving; human-robot collaboration at pick stations with Sparrow arm."]}]
41:["$","p","p-16",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Open questions"}],":"]}]
42:["$","ul","ul-11",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Formal safety certification for HRC: Speed-and-separation monitoring doesn't address all failure modes (robot predicts incorrectly, worker surprised by movement)."}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"How to design intuitive robot communication (gesture, sound, light) that doesn't add cognitive load to workers?"}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"Long-term ergonomic impacts of sustained HRC: Limited longitudinal studies."}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":"Cross-cultural differences in comfort with robots: Safety thresholds calibrated to specific populations may not generalize."}],"\n"]}]
43:["$","p","p-17",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Key papers"}],":"]}]
44:["$","ul","ul-12",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":["Lorenzini, M. et al. (2023). Ergonomic human-robot collaboration in industry. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"Frontiers in Robotics and AI"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":["Javdani, S. et al. (2018). Shared Autonomy via Hindsight Optimization. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"IJRR"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":["ISO/TS 15066:2016. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"Robots and robotic devices — Collaborative robots"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":["Villani, V. et al. (2018). Survey on Human-Robot Collaboration in Industrial Settings. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"Mechatronics"}],"."]}],"\n"]}]
45:["$","hr","hr-5",{}]
46:["$","h2","h2-5",{"children":"5. Explainable Automation (XAI)"}]
47:["$","p","p-18",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Why it matters"}],": Black-box AI decisions in automation undermine operator trust, prevent regulatory compliance, and make debugging nearly impossible. The EU AI Act (enforcement August 2026) mandates explanations for high-risk AI systems. Industrial operators need to understand why a system took an action to validate, correct, and trust it."]}]
48:["$","p","p-19",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Current state-of-the-art (2025)"}],":"]}]
49:["$","ul","ul-13",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"SHAP (SHapley Additive exPlanations)"}],": Feature attribution method providing theoretically grounded credit assignment. Industry standard for tabular models. Computational cost: O(2^n) exact, O(samples) approximation [Lundberg & Lee, 2017]."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"LIME"}],": Local interpretable model-agnostic explanations — fit an interpretable model around individual predictions [Ribeiro et al., 2016]."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Concept Activation Vectors (TCAV)"}],": Explains CNN decisions in terms of human-defined visual concepts (e.g., \"object has a handle\") [Kim et al., 2018]."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Integrated Gradients"}],": Attribution method for neural networks; satisfies axioms of sensitivity and implementation invariance."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-4",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Counterfactual explanations"}],": \"The loan was denied because income was $45K; had income been $52K, it would have been approved.\" More actionable than feature importance. Growing in industrial and financial applications."]}],"\n"]}]
4a:["$","p","p-20",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Open questions"}],":"]}]
4b:["$","ul","ul-14",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Do explanations actually increase human trust? User studies show mixed results—explanations can decrease trust when wrong [Poursabzi-Sangdeh et al., 2021]."}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"How to explain complex multi-step automation workflows spanning dozens of decisions?"}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"Systematic interpretability-performance trade-off characterization: How much accuracy do we lose for full interpretability?"}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":"Real-time XAI for safety-critical systems: SHAP computation takes milliseconds to seconds; insufficient for <50ms control loops."}],"\n"]}]
4c:["$","p","p-21",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Key papers"}],":"]}]
4d:["$","ul","ul-15",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":["Lundberg, S.M. & Lee, S.I. (2017). A unified approach to interpreting model predictions. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"NeurIPS 2017"}]," (SHAP)."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":["Ribeiro, M.T. et al. (2016). Why should I trust you? Explaining predictions of any classifier. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"KDD 2016"}]," (LIME)."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":["Arrieta, A.B. et al. (2020). Explainable AI: Concepts, taxonomies, applications. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"Information Fusion"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":["EU AI Act (2024). ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"Regulation on Artificial Intelligence"}],", Articles 13-14 (Transparency requirements)."]}],"\n"]}]
4e:["$","hr","hr-6",{}]
4f:["$","h2","h2-6",{"children":"6. Edge AI Optimization"}]
50:["$","p","p-22",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Why it matters"}],": Industrial and robotic applications require real-time inference (<50ms) on embedded hardware with tight power budgets (<5–30W). State-of-the-art models (GPT-4-scale, large vision transformers) require data centers. The gap between model capability and deployable compute is a core research frontier."]}]
51:["$","p","p-23",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Current state-of-the-art (2025)"}],":"]}]
52:["$","ul","ul-16",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Quantization"}],": INT8 models reduce memory 75%, increase throughput 4× vs. FP32 with <1% accuracy loss on most vision tasks. INT4 emerging (2024) for LLM inference on edge devices."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Structured pruning"}],": Remove entire filters or attention heads (not just individual weights); 50–90% parameter reduction with 2–5% accuracy loss on CNN benchmarks."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Knowledge distillation"}],": Train a small \"student\" to mimic a large \"teacher.\" DistilBERT retains 97% of BERT performance at 40% size."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Neural Architecture Search (NAS)"}],": Automatically find architectures optimized for target hardware (EfficientNet, MobileNetV3, YOLO-Nano)."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-4",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Hardware platforms (2025)"}],":","\n",["$","ul","ul-0",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"NVIDIA Jetson Orin NX: 100 TOPS, 10–25W — flagship research/robotics platform."}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"NVIDIA Jetson Thor (announced 2024): 2000 TOPS, targets humanoid robots."}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"Google Coral TPU: 4 TOPS sustained, 0.5–2W — ultra-efficient for classification-only tasks."}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":"Qualcomm RB5: 15 TOPS, cellular connectivity — robotics + connected devices."}],"\n",["$","li","li-4",{"children":"Intel Loihi 2 (neuromorphic, 2022): Sparse inference at 1000× lower energy than GPU for specific workloads."}],"\n"]}],"\n"]}],"\n"]}]
53:["$","p","p-24",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Performance benchmarks (2025)"}],":"]}]
54:["$","ul","ul-17",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"ResNet-50 on Jetson Orin NX: 8ms latency"}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"YOLOv8-nano on Jetson Orin NX: 3ms latency (333 FPS)"}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"LLaMA-7B INT4 on Jetson AGX Orin: ~15 tokens/sec"}],"\n"]}]
55:["$","p","p-25",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Open questions"}],":"]}]
56:["$","ul","ul-18",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Closing the performance gap for transformer models on edge (attention is O(n²) — poorly suited to fixed SIMD hardware)."}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"Neuromorphic computing for event cameras: Sparse, asynchronous visual processing theoretically ideal for robotics but programming models are immature."}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"Federated learning for edge model improvement: Update models from distributed robot deployments without centralizing data."}],"\n"]}]
57:["$","p","p-26",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Key papers"}],":"]}]
58:["$","ul","ul-19",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":["Han, S. et al. (2016). Deep Compression: Compressing DNNs with Pruning, Quantization and Huffman Coding. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"ICLR 2016"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":["Howard, A. et al. (2019). Searching for MobileNetV3. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"ICCV 2019"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":["Hinton, G. et al. (2015). Distilling the knowledge in a neural network. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"arXiv:1503.02531"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":"NVIDIA (2025). Jetson Orin Technical Reference Manual. NVIDIA Corporation."}],"\n"]}]
59:["$","hr","hr-7",{}]
5a:["$","h2","h2-7",{"children":"7. Multi-Agent Coordination"}]
5b:["$","p","p-27",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Why it matters"}],": Modern automation increasingly involves fleets of robots (Amazon: 750K+ warehouse robots), drone swarms, and distributed IoT networks. Centralized coordination becomes a single point of failure and communication bottleneck. Decentralized coordination that achieves global objectives from local interactions is a fundamental open problem."]}]
5c:["$","p","p-28",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Current state-of-the-art (2025)"}],":"]}]
5d:["$","ul","ul-20",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Decentralized Multi-Agent RL (Dec-MARL)"}],": QMIX, MAPPO, MADDPG for cooperative multi-agent problems. Scales to ~100 agents in simulation; real-world deployment at 15–20 agents."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Graph Neural Networks for coordination"}],": GNNs capture agent topology; scale better to variable team sizes [Sukhbaatar et al., 2016; Li et al., 2021]."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Hierarchical coordination"}],": High-level coordinator decomposes tasks; low-level agents execute locally (MapReduce-style decomposition for robotics)."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Swarm robotics"}],": Stigmergic coordination (pheromone analog, shared environment state); scales to 1000+ simple agents (Kilobot demonstrations at 1024 units)."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-4",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Multi-robot SLAM"}],": Distributed mapping where robots share map information — CoSLAM, Multi-Robot Cartographer."]}],"\n"]}]
5e:["$","p","p-29",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Real deployments"}],":"]}]
5f:["$","ul","ul-21",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Amazon: 750,000+ robots, primarily centralized (KIVA/Amazon Robotics system assigns tasks via central scheduler). Research challenge is decentralized fallback."}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"DJI Swarm: 100+ drone light shows (synchronized via pre-planned trajectories, not truly reactive swarms)."}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"Power grid demand response: Millions of prosumers (grid-interactive devices) coordinated via market mechanisms — the largest real-world multi-agent system."}],"\n"]}]
60:["$","p","p-30",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Open questions"}],":"]}]
61:["$","ul","ul-22",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Emergent behavior verification: In swarms, global behavior emerges from local rules. Proving safety properties of emergent behaviors is extremely hard."}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"Communication constraints: Real wireless channels have latency, packet loss, limited bandwidth. Most MARL assumes perfect communication."}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"Heterogeneous teams: Coordinating robots with different capabilities, speeds, and sensor modalities without centralization."}],"\n"]}]
62:["$","p","p-31",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Key papers"}],":"]}]
63:["$","ul","ul-23",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":["Rashid, T. et al. (2018). QMIX: Monotonic Value Function Factorisation for Deep Multi-Agent RL. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"ICML 2018"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":["Yu, C. et al. (2022). The Surprising Effectiveness of PPO in Cooperative Multi-Agent Games. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"NeurIPS 2022"}]," (MAPPO)."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":["Bullo, F. et al. (2009). ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"Distributed Control of Robotic Networks"}],". Princeton University Press."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":["Dorigo, M. et al. (2021). Swarm Robotics: Past, Present, and Future. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"Proceedings of IEEE"}],"."]}],"\n"]}]
64:["$","hr","hr-8",{}]
65:["$","h2","h2-8",{"children":"8. Foundation Models for Physical AI"}]
66:["$","p","p-32",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Why it matters"}],": LLMs and VLMs trained on internet-scale data show emergent generalization to new tasks. Applying this to robotics could overcome the data bottleneck that limits task-specific robot learning. This is arguably the most active area of robotics research in 2024–2026."]}]
67:["$","p","p-33",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Current state-of-the-art (2025-2026)"}],":"]}]
68:["$","ul","ul-24",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"RT-2 (2023, Google DeepMind)"}],": VLM fine-tuned on robot data; 62% success on novel tasks. Emergent chain-of-thought reasoning for object manipulation [Brohan et al., 2023]."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"RT-X (2023)"}],": Single policy across 22 robot embodiments from Open X-Embodiment dataset (1M+ trajectories). Cross-embodiment generalization demonstrated [O'Neill et al., 2023]."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"π0 (2024, Physical Intelligence)"}],": Flow-matching policy with VLM backbone; dexterous manipulation (laundry, box assembly) — qualitatively ahead of prior methods."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Octo (2024, Berkeley)"}],": Open-source generalist policy; outperforms baselines on 9/14 benchmark tasks. [Octo team, 2024, arXiv:2405.12213]."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-4",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Gemini Robotics (2025, Google DeepMind)"}],": Gemini 2.0 with robotics fine-tuning; demonstrated multi-step tasks with natural language instruction following in unstructured environments."]}],"\n"]}]
69:["$","p","p-34",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Open questions"}],":"]}]
6a:["$","ul","ul-25",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Data scaling laws for robotics: Does more diverse robot data always improve generalization? (LLM scaling laws may not hold for physical interaction.)"}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"Dexterous manipulation at human level: Current success rates 60–75% on complex grasps; humans achieve 95%+."}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"Long-horizon planning with foundation models: Tasks requiring 50+ sequential steps remain challenging for LLM planners due to error accumulation."}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":"Safety of foundation model-controlled robots: Black-box VLMs are difficult to formally verify."}],"\n"]}]
6b:["$","p","p-35",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Key papers"}],":"]}]
6c:["$","ul","ul-26",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":["Brohan, A. et al. (2023). RT-2: Vision-Language-Action Models. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"arXiv:2307.15818"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":["Octo Model Team (2024). Octo: An Open-Source Generalist Robot Policy. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"arXiv:2405.12213"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":["O'Neill, J. et al. (2023). Open X-Embodiment. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"arXiv:2310.08864"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":["Doshi, R. et al. (2024). π0: A Vision-Language-Action Flow Model for General Robot Control. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"arXiv:2410.24164"}],"."]}],"\n"]}]
6d:["$","hr","hr-9",{}]
6e:["$","h2","h2-9",{"children":"9. Autonomous Policy and Ethics"}]
6f:["$","p","p-36",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Why it matters"}],": As automation systems make consequential decisions (medical triage, resource allocation, law enforcement prediction, autonomous weapons), the question of who is morally and legally responsible for those decisions is unresolved. This is not a philosophical exercise—it directly affects regulation, insurance, and liability law."]}]
70:["$","p","p-37",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Core problems"}],":"]}]
71:["$","p","p-38",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Trolley problem variants for automation"}],":"]}]
72:["$","ul","ul-27",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Autonomous vehicle: unavoidable collision — minimize total casualties or protect occupant? (MIT Moral Machine study: 2.3M participants across 233 countries showed significant cultural variation in preferred outcomes [Awad et al., 2018].)"}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"Medical triage AI: prioritize by prognosis or equity? Age vs. life-years-saved trade-offs."}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"No algorithm is value-neutral. Encoding a preference is itself a moral choice."}],"\n"]}]
73:["$","p","p-39",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Liability in autonomous system failures"}],":"]}]
74:["$","ul","ul-28",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Traditional products liability: manufacturer liable for defective products."}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"AV law evolving: Mercedes explicitly accepted liability for Drive Pilot L3 failures (2023) — first manufacturer to do so. This sets a precedent."}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"Algorithmic accountability: GDPR Article 22 provides right not to be subject to solely automated decisions with legal/significant effects. EU AI Act extends this."}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":"Open question: Who is liable for a learned behavior that was never explicitly programmed?"}],"\n"]}]
75:["$","p","p-40",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Transparency requirements"}],":"]}]
76:["$","ul","ul-29",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"EU AI Act: High-risk AI systems must be transparent to deployers; affected persons have right to explanation."}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"Algorithmic auditing: Third-party audits for consequential AI systems. NIST AI RMF provides a framework; mandatory auditing emerging in sector-specific regulations."}],"\n"]}]
77:["$","p","p-41",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Autonomous weapons"}],":"]}]
78:["$","ul","ul-30",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"LAWS (Lethal Autonomous Weapon Systems): UN Convention on Certain Conventional Weapons (CCW) discussions ongoing since 2014; no binding treaty as of 2026."}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"Meaningful human control: ICRC position that lethal force decisions must retain human judgment. Definition of \"meaningful\" contested."}],"\n"]}]
79:["$","p","p-42",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Key references"}],":"]}]
7a:["$","ul","ul-31",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":["Awad, E. et al. (2018). The Moral Machine experiment. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"Nature"}],", 563, 59–64."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":["EU AI Act (2024). ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"Regulation on Artificial Intelligence"}],". European Parliament."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":["ICRC (2021). ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning in Armed Conflict"}],". Geneva."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":["Mittelstadt, B. et al. (2016). The ethics of algorithms: Mapping the debate. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"Big Data & Society"}],"."]}],"\n"]}]
7b:["$","hr","hr-10",{}]
7c:["$","h2","h2-10",{"children":"Frontier 9: Quantum-Assisted Automation"}]
7d:["$","p","p-43",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"The Core Problem"}],": The optimization problems inherent in global supply chains, robotic routing, and deep learning for automation systems suffer from combinatorial explosion. Classical compute clusters hit hard physical limits when calculating optimal paths for millions of nodes (e.g., the Traveling Salesperson Problem)."]}]
7e:["$","p","p-44",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"State-of-the-Art (May 2026)"}],":"]}]
7f:["$","ul","ul-32",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Quantum Routing (Q-Routing)"}],": Early hybrid algorithms using Quantum Annealing (D-Wave) and Noisy Intermediate-Scale Quantum (NISQ) gates to optimize fleets of thousands of AGVs simultaneously, reducing computation time from hours to seconds for complex constraints."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Variational Quantum Eigensolver (VQE) for Materials"}],": Using quantum algorithms to simulate and discover novel materials for robotic batteries and lightweight sensors."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Quantum Machine Learning (QML)"}],": Speeding up the training phase of Foundation Models used in autonomous systems via quantum kernels."]}],"\n"]}]
80:["$","p","p-45",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Key references"}],":"]}]
81:["$","ul","ul-33",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":["Biamonte, J. et al. (2017). Quantum machine learning. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"Nature"}],", 549(7671), 195-202."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":["Preskill, J. (2018). Quantum Computing in the NISQ era and beyond. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"Quantum"}],", 2, 79."]}],"\n"]}]
82:["$","hr","hr-11",{}]
83:["$","h2","h2-11",{"children":"Frontier 10: Closed-Loop Scientific Discovery (\"Cloud Labs\")"}]
84:["$","p","p-46",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"The Core Problem"}],": The scientific method is historically manual, slow, and prone to human error or non-reproducibility. While data analysis has been computerized, the physical loop of synthesizing, testing, and observing in biology and chemistry remains a bottleneck."]}]
85:["$","p","p-47",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"State-of-the-Art (May 2026)"}],":"]}]
86:["$","ul","ul-34",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Self-Driving Laboratories"}],": AI systems that formulate hypotheses (e.g., a new battery compound or protein sequence), command robotic liquid handlers and synthesizers to physically create it, autonomously run assays, process the data, and refine the hypothesis—without human intervention."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Scale"}],": Commercial \"Cloud Labs\" (e.g., Emerald Cloud Lab) where scientists simply write code to orchestrate thousands of automated chemical instruments 24/7."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Impact"}],": Drug discovery timelines reduced from years to months; accelerated discovery of stable electrolytes for solid-state batteries."]}],"\n"]}]
87:["$","p","p-48",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Key references"}],":"]}]
88:["$","ul","ul-35",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":["Szymanski, V. et al. (2023). Autonomous laboratories for scientific discovery. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"Nature Materials"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":["Jumper, J. et al. (2024). Highly accurate protein structure prediction with AlphaFold 3. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"Nature"}],"."]}],"\n"]}]
89:["$","h2","h2-12",{"children":"Frontier 11: Neuromorphic Robotics & Event-Based Vision"}]
8a:["$","p","p-49",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"The Core Problem"}],": Traditional robots perceive the world through frame-based cameras (e.g., 60 frames per second). This creates massive data redundancy (processing unchanged background pixels) and introduces latency that is fatal for high-speed drones or robotic arms reacting to sudden obstacles. Furthermore, processing these dense matrices requires high-wattage GPUs, which drain battery life rapidly."]}]
8b:["$","p","p-50",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"State-of-the-Art (May 2026)"}],":"]}]
8c:["$","ul","ul-36",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Event-Based Vision (Dynamic Vision Sensors)"}],": Instead of capturing frames, neuromorphic cameras only fire asynchronous \"events\" when individual pixels detect a change in brightness. This biomimetic approach (mirroring the human retina) enables microsecond latency, zero motion blur, and a dynamic range that handles both glaring sun and dark shadows simultaneously."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs)"}],": Paired with event cameras, edge chips like Intel Loihi process information via neural \"spikes\" rather than continuous floating-point operations."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Impact"}],": 2026 research demonstrates event-based vision enabling drones to dodge thrown objects at high speeds while consuming milliwatts of power—a feat impossible with standard Deep Learning architectures."]}],"\n"]}]
8d:["$","p","p-51",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Key references"}],":"]}]
8e:["$","ul","ul-37",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":["Gallego, G. et al. (2022). Event-based vision: A survey. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"IEEE TPAMI"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":[["$","em","em-0",{"children":"Brain Sciences"}]," (April 2026). \"Event-Based Vision at the Edge: A Review\" (SNNs for robotics)."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":[["$","em","em-0",{"children":"IEEE Transactions on Human-Machine Systems"}]," (2026). \"Applications of Neuromorphic/Event Camera in Robotics With Human in Loop\"."]}],"\n"]}]
8f:["$","hr","hr-12",{}]
90:["$","h2","h2-13",{"children":"Frontier 12: Brain-Computer Interface (BCI) Teleoperation"}]
91:["$","p","p-52",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"The Core Problem"}],": Human-Robot Collaboration (HRC) in hazardous environments (nuclear decommissioning, deep-sea, space) relies on joysticks or haptic gloves. These interfaces are low-bandwidth, unintuitive, and suffer from severe cognitive load when operating highly dexterous multi-fingered robotic hands."]}]
92:["$","p","p-53",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"State-of-the-Art (May 2026)"}],":"]}]
93:["$","ul","ul-38",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Thought-to-Action"}],": Capitalizing on the successful FDA human trials by Neuralink and Synchron, robotics researchers have begun closing the loop. Motor intent is decoded directly from the motor cortex to command the joint angles of a robotic arm in real-time."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Bidirectional BCI"}],": The holy grail of 2026 BCI robotics is bidirectional feedback—the robot's tactile sensors transmitting pressure data back into the human's somatosensory cortex, allowing the operator to \"feel\" what the robot is touching thousands of miles away."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Impact"}],": True robotic avatars, drastically lowering the training time required to operate complex, high-degree-of-freedom robotic systems."]}],"\n"]}]
94:["$","p","p-54",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Key references"}],":"]}]
95:["$","ul","ul-39",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":["Musk, E. & Neuralink (2019). An integrated brain-machine interface platform with thousands of channels. ",["$","em","em-0",{"children":"J. Med. Internet Res"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"Recent clinical trials and robotics integration (2025–2026)."}],"\n"]}]
96:["$","hr","hr-13",{}]
97:["$","p","p-55",{"children":["$","em","em-0",{"children":"Last updated: 2026-05-07 | v2.2 — Added Frontiers 11 (Neuromorphic) & 12 (BCI) based on 2026 breakthroughs"}]}]
